those things fixed right. Here, hook him up. So 
with that, I don't know whether you heard the rest

15:19.063 --> 15:23.568
of the briefing or not.

15:30.174 --> 15:30.775
We had a We've jumped four years, but he's a very 
outspoken man, which is great. By the way, he was an

15:41.999 --> 15:46.123
Ohio State civil engineer. I don't know whether 
you knew that or not, but even engineers become

15:47.525 --> 15:53.611
pretty good leaders. We were getting ready to 
modernize the officer's club at Bowling. There

16:02.783 --> 16:07.507
were a couple of concepts as to how to do it. And oh 
boy, we're seven or eight years ahead now. Because

16:12.652 --> 16:17.216
by that time, I was in the Secretary of the Air Force 
office. And there was a group in his office with a

16:17.236 --> 16:23.562
model of the officer's club. And there must have 
been about 16 or 18 officers, including me. They

16:32.247 --> 16:35.551
got to talking about the concept. And now, see, 
here everybody works for him except me, and I work

16:36.872 --> 16:42.819
for the Secretary of the Air Force. And one of these 
guys says, General LeMay, Mr. Zuckert, who is the

16:43.580 --> 16:52.390
Secretary of the Air Force, Mr. Zuckert thinks 
that we ought to do so-and-so.

16:54.833 --> 16:55.674
Oh, you know that stuff. Oh, you go tell Mr. Zuckert 
to piss off a rope. Now he's talking about my boss.

