24:19.821 --> 24:22.644
Okay, so then you went to France right after that in 
1956. That was terrific. Were you eager to get

24:24.006 --> 24:25.468
overseas again? Well, I hadn't been overseas. 
They offered me Alaska or France and though in my

24:28.692 --> 24:39.685
master's study at A&M I studied Creopediology, 
which is permafrost, I chose France. A little bit

24:45.058 --> 24:48.904
nicer place to live. A little more action. The 
organizations are larger. You got a two-star in

24:55.112 --> 24:57.776
command in Alaska. You got a four-star in command 
in Europe. I

25:01.201 --> 25:08.071
think your chances are better in Europe. We went 
over and I was a resident engineer at two bases. One

25:13.048 --> 25:19.695
has already been completed, but we were 
lengthening the runway and doing some more

25:13.048 --> 25:19.695
facility work. Where was that? That was Shomal. 
Shomal happens to be one of the locations that

25:23.179 --> 25:39.017
Black Jack Pershing had his headquarters during 
World War I. Shomal, Sur Marne, the Marne River.

25:40.027 --> 25:50.482
The other one was Shalon Battery, which was a brand 
new base that had only a runway and a few

25:40.027 --> 25:50.482
facilities. And it was a NATO base. That's what 
NATO gave us here, a runway and a few facilities.

25:58.013 --> 26:02.439
And we were pouring American dollars into 
building another base. And that's where I spent

26:03.681 --> 26:08.127
most of my time.

26:09.777 --> 26:38.653
My deputy was an Army civil servant, and I worked 
with the French ,, which is roads and bridges, who

